      </p>
      <p>
        In the immortal words of Father William to his nephew, as penned by=
 Lewis Carroll, who was a mathematician:
      </p>
      <p align=3D"center">
        I have answered three questions and that is enough,
      </p>
      <p align=3D"center">
        Said the sage, don't give yourself airs.
      </p>
      <p align=3D"center">
        Do you think I can listen all day to such stuff?
      </p>
      <p align=3D"center">
        Be off or I'll kick you downstairs!
